SIMPLE: seduction
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Seduction
<hw>Se*duc*tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>seductio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>s⟦eacute⟧duction</ets>. <ets>See</ets>
<er>Seduce</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of seducing; enticement
to wrong doing; enticement to fail in some duty.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <specif>Specifically:</specif> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The
offense of inducing a woman to consent to unlawful sexual intercourse,
by enticements which overcome her scruples; the wrong or crime of
persuading a woman to surrender her chastity.</def>
<mark>[Archaic]</mark> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Any successful enticement to
engage in some sexual activity, especially intercourse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>That which seduces, or is adapted to seduce; means
of leading astray; <as>as, the <ex>seductions</ex> of
wealth</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Seductive</ent>⟦br⟧
